was
a
heavy
metal
door.
The
iron
key
was
in
the
lock,
and
the
door
hung
slightly
ajar.
He
pushed,
and
the
door
creaked
open.
The
air
beyond
felt
cold.
As
Langdon
stepped
across
the
threshold
into
murky
darkness,
he
realized
he
was
now
outside.
"I
was
just
coming
to
get
you,"
Katherine
said,
smiling
at
