We
are
builders,
he
thought.
We
are
creators.
Since
the
beginning
of
time,
man
had
sensed
there
was
something
special
about
himself
something
more.
He
had
longed
for
powers
he
did
not
possess.
He
had
dreamed
of
flying,
of
healing,
and
of
transforming
